Java program which displays falling snow in multiple windows.

The simulated snow falls within a shared view/scene and the windows become
viewports (windows!) to that scene. This means that snowflakes may fall from
one window to another.

    $ java -cp target\snow-1.0-SNAPSHOT-jar-with-dependencies.jar \
    -Djava.library.path=./lib/opencv/x64 \
    -DfaceDetectionConfigurationFilePath=./src/main/resources/haarcascade_frontalface_alt.xml snow.weather.WeatherApplication 100,100,1800,900